column5: A little boy got on the bus,  sat next to a man reading a book, and noticed he had his collar on backwards.  The little boy asked why he wore his collar that way.  The man, who was a priest, said, " I am a  Father." The little boy replied, "My Daddy doesn't wear his collar  like that."  The priest looked up from his book and answered "I am  the Father of many."  The boy said, "My Dad has 4 boys, 4 girls and two  grandchildren and he doesn't wear his collar that way."  The priest,  getting impatient, said, "I am the Father of hundreds" and went back to reading  his book.  The little boy sat quietly thinking for a while, then  leaned over and said, "Maybe you should wear your pants backwards instead of  your collar."
Wouldn't you just love to see the expression on priest's face after hearing that response.
